texts.text: >Jeng Yun manages to barely dodge Taisei's attacks.
Damn! This one's strong!
Taisei, I must strike back! Please forgive me! Hah!
Gah...!
No...! I will not be defeated...!
*Wince*
Jeng Yun, are you okay?!
I'll be fine! It's just a scratch.
>Jeng Yun and Taisei both fall to their knees.
*Groan*
*Pant*
(I need to make him come to his senses...!)
(Oh, right...)
>Jeng Yun remembers something and sits back up.
Fool! You dare leave yourself open like that!
Yo, there's too many demons! Jeng Yun, come back!
No. If we do not act now, Taisei will be lost forever.
The fate of Tokyo depends on this. I will save him even if it kills me.
Yo! What happened to what we just said about that?!
Don't worry. I believe in him.
Sitting down... At a time like this? You really are a fool!
Why do you not attack...?
>Taisei collapses after spending his last ounce of energy.
(Sitting... Wait... That... Reminds me...)
>A few years ago at the Yamamoto residence. Jeng Yun sits quietly.
Meditation...?
Yes. Jogan taught me.
I did not know Japanese martial arts involved so much meditation.
It helps us craft better swords and hone our fighting skills,
but I don't really understand how.
I enjoy doing this.
It's nice to take some time and look back at myself or my past.
Like cleaning up the clutter in my mind.
I can feel why I am here, why I fight...
And what I need to do...
Why I fight...? And what I need to do...?
"One that cuts down even the most ferocious enemies."
Father never said anything regarding what I said.
He wanted to tell me that I was mistaken.
"It only takes its outward appearance into consideration,"
"and is a failed experiment that happens to be able to cut well."
What he said. The part about outward appearances...
Was he was trying to tell me about dealing with my inner self?
If a truly great sword can cut down even the most ferocious enemies...
What is my...? What is the enemy of the Yamamoto Clan?
The demon from before is gone. It doesn't feel like an enemy.
What was that thing? Was it really even a demon?
When Jeng Yun said, "Don't blame the bear. Blame the evil spirit!"
I only cared about being able to slice through everything.
But was I actually seeing what I should be cutting...
Or who I should be considering my true enemy...?
>Taisei stands and walks towards the seated demon.
>The demon stays still and does not seem willing to move.
If you will not resist then...!
>Taisei readies his sword and attempts a big swing.
Jeng Yun!!
*Scream*
>He does not slice the demon, but the negative energy around him.
You're, Jung Yun... Aren't you?
>At that moment, he starts to see Jeng Yun instead of a demon.
You're back, Taisei...
Even after the bear incident, you're doing crazy things...
>Futsunushi asks his question once more...
What is a sword to you?
>Taisei proudly answers...
A sword is my heart!
If a wielder believes they must cut everything, then their judgment is clouded.
They will ultimately cause harm to everything in their path!
However, protecting this country means we must have the right convictions.
We must become the very blade that protects this land!
We, the Yamamoto Clan, must be the ones that fulfill this duty!
You have finally looked inward.
I acknowledge thee as worthy and give my blessing as the sword deity.
>Taisei's sword glows vibrantly as Futsunushi empowers it.
Hah!
>Taisei swings the sword and the negative energy around him dissipates.
>As it subsides, the mist begins to fade as well.
(Father was trying to tell me this the entire time...)
(But I never tried to actually listen to him.)
>The source of the energy comes into view.
There! The source of all this!
>The remaining energy all coalesces into one demon.
Blast! I was so close to being fully revived!
You again!
No different from last time, I guess...

*Groan*
Just looking at that thing is making me sick.
Agreed! It's the most vile thing in existence!
Yo, I was hopin' to never see you again.

*Laugh*
I warned you, did I not?
As long as your toxic desires continue to exist, I shall persist!
Shit. Right.
Yo, it's you from that time Tokyo was flooded with poison,
and appeared after everyone's malice gave you the power to...!
I see. You are the foe that I must vanquish!
You damn Yamamotos! How many times have you foiled my plans?!
I may not be fully regenerated, but I can at least take you down with me!
